text: Whitty is a remote rural locality and civil parish of Evelyn County in far northwest New South Wales. Map of the County of Evelyn : Western Division. located at 30°12′34″S 141°05′06″E. ==Geography== The geography of the Parish is mostly the flat, arid landscape of the Channel Country. The nearest town is Tibooburra to the east, which is on the Silver City Highway and lies south of the Sturt National Park.Olive Downs campground. The western boundary of the parish is the South Australian border. ==History== The Parish is on the traditional lands of the WadigaliAboriginal Heritage, Corner Country History & Heritage.Tindale, Norman Barnett (1974). Aboriginal peoples.David R Horton (creator), © Aboriginal Studies Press, AIATSIS, and Auslig/Sinclair, Knight, Merz, 1996. The parish has a Köppen climate classification of BWh (Hot desert). (direct: Final Revised Paper) Charles Sturt passed through the area during 1845,Sturt's Central Australian Expedition.
